{"type":"message","id":"7a9b3f6e","parentId":"5350f313","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:03:39.066Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5mc5adwu0zfm_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 030013\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state:\r\n\r\n1. The goals document shows Phase 0 and Phase 1 as complete\r\n2. The key pending action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n3. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nLooking at the logs directory, there are several pulse logs. The next action should be implementing the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what needs to be done for the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action should be creating a TIC classifier. This is a concrete file edit/create action.\r\n\r\nI should create a script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing) content\r\n3. Classifies content\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me implement this in PowerShell since the environment is Windows-based (pulse.ps1 exists).\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step, but I need to create the classifier implementation first before it can run on the pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs to identify invariant vs variant content and attempt next-pulse prediction. This advances the Phase 1 Compression-Causal Duality experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\n# Phase 1: Compression-Causal Duality Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [int]$RecentCount = 20,\r\n    [double]$Threshold = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing last $RecentCount pulse logs for invariant patterns...\"\r\n\r\n# Collect pulse logs sorted by time\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object Name -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $RecentCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 3) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"Need at least 3 pulse logs, found $($pulseFiles.Count)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# Parse each pulse into structured content\r\nfunction Parse-Pulse {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    $lines = Get-Content $Path\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key sections via regex\r\n    $observation = if ($content -match '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)') { $matches[1].Trim() } else { \"\" }\r\n    $action = if ($content -match '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)') { $matches[1].Trim() } else { \"\" }\r\n    $mutation = if ($content -match '(?s)### MUTATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=```\\s*$|\\Z)') { $matches[1].Trim() } else { \"\" }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Path = $Path\r\n        Raw = $content\r\n        Lines = $lines\r\n        Observation = $observation\r\n        Action = $action\r\n        Mutation = $mutation\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Parse all pulses\r\n$pulses = $pulseFiles | ForEach-Object { Parse-Pulse $_.FullName }\r\n\r\n# Tokenize text for comparison\r\nfunction Tokenize {\r\n    param([string]$Text)\r\n    $clean = $Text.ToLower() -replace '[^\\w\\s]', ' '\r\n    return [System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]::new(\r\n        ($clean -split '\\s+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }),\r\n        [System.StringComparer]::OrdinalIgnoreCase\r\n    )\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate Jaccard similarity between two token sets\r\nfunction JaccardSimilarity {\r\n    param([System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]$Set1, \r\n           [System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]$Set2)\r\n    \r\n    $intersection = [System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]::new($Set1)\r\n    $intersection.IntersectWith($Set2)\r\n    \r\n    $union = [System.Collections.Generic.HashSet[string]]::new($Set1)\r\n    $union.UnionWith($Set2)\r\n    \r\n    if ($union.Count -eq 0) { return 0 }\r\n    return $intersection.Count / $union.Count\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Categorize content as INVARIANT or VARIANT based on consistency\r\nfunction Classify-Content {\r\n    param([array]$ContentArray, [string]$ContentType)\r\n    \r\n    $tokenSets = $ContentArray | ForEach-Object { Tokenize $_ }\r\n    $n = $tokenSets.Count\r\n    \r\n    if ($n -lt 2) { return @{ Type = \"VARIANT\"; Score = 0; StableTokens = @() } }\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate pairwise similarities\r\n    $similarities = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $n - 1; $i++) {\r\n        for ($j = $i + 1; $j -lt $n; $j++) {\r\n            $similarities += JaccardSimilarity $tokenSets[$i] $tokenSets[$j]\r\n        }\r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:00:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335819063}}
