{"type":"message","id":"f8f7441c","parentId":"9c455400","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:04:38.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the TIC experiment needs pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md` format, but the actual logs are in `memory/session/pulse_*.md` format. \n\nThe most concrete next action is to either:\n1. Create a `logs` symlink or copy to `memory/session/` from `logs/` \n2. Or update the TIC script to read from `memory/session/`\n\nSince the `test-tic.ps1` script is already written and looks correct, the simplest fix is to create the `logs` directory and copy/link the session pulse logs there. Or even simpler - create symlinks.\n\nBut wait - I need to do this as a mutation. Let me think about what file to edit/create.\n\n\nI think the best approach is to create the `logs` directory and symlink it to `memory/session/`, then update the TIC script to read from there. Actually, the simpler path is just to copy the pulse log files over directly - that's a concrete file operation I can do right now.\n\nLooking at the pulse log timestamps, the newest one is `pulse_2026-03-24 030316.md` from the most recent cycle. So my action is to create the `logs` directory and copy the session pulse logs into it, then verify the TIC script runs properly.","thinkingSignature":"710d3cd2a5ef827ffd7afed14caff7e98c6c6542814c608b496bdef844bf56f0"},{"type":"text","text":"The TIC classifier exists but the `logs/` directory with pulse logs doesn't. The most concrete next step is bridging that gap — copying session pulse logs into `logs/` so the TIC experiment can run.\n\nLet me take that action now:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vejn31cuef25_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\logs -Force | Out-Null; Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\ | Copy-Item -Destination C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\logs\\ -PassThru | ForEach-Objec